OL,3,CHas International Women's Day lost its
OL,4,Csignificance?
OL,6,FBut the -based charity said women are
OL,7,Fangry that the day is being "hijacked
OL,8,Fby organisations who superficially
OL,9,Fmark IWD through one-off events and
OL,10,Fsocial media marketing, while their
OL,11,Fpolicies and day-to-day practices
OL,12,Fconsistently neglect the specific
OL,13,Fneeds and challenges faced by women."
OL,15,FSue Oshikanlu, Chair of The Womens
OL,16,FOrganisation, said, "Women are tired
OL,17,Fof the constant stream of events,
OL,18,Fpanels and social media noise which is
OL,19,Fa convenient distraction from taking
OL,20,Fconcrete actions that could truly
OL,21,Fimpact women's lives."
